package com.example.sort;

import java.util.Arrays;

public class BubbleSort {
    public static void bubbleSort(int[] arr) {
        int n = arr.length;
        for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < n - i - 1; j++) {
                if (arr[j] > arr[j + 1]) {
                    int temp = arr[j];
                    arr[j] = arr[j + 1];
                    arr[j + 1] = temp;
                }
            }
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {5, 12, 3, 18, 7};
        System.out.println("Original array: " + Arrays.toString(arr));
        bubbleSort(arr);
        System.out.println("Sorted array: " + Arrays.toString(arr));
    }
}
```
This code defines a `BubbleSort` class with a `bubbleSort` method that implements the bubble sort algorithm to sort an array of integers in ascending order. The `main` method demonstrates the usage of the `bubbleSort` method by sorting an example array and printing the original and sorted arrays.
